the FRÜHLING has given South Australia a wintry surprise , with fierce displays and strong winds affecting flights from Adelaide Airport .
in the evening to 9 p.m. , another 5mm of rain fell to the city , after 6.6mm that had already been down on Sunday night .
the last rainfall was the result of a series of short , stormy showers , including a bus that began just before 8pm and caused nearly 4mm of rainfall in about 10 minutes .
after the winter last week caused an early dose of spring , temperatures in the city fell again to a peak of just 15.8 ° C.
bad weather conditions have likely led to the late landing of a flight from Virgin Airlines from Melbourne to Adelaide .
the plane should have landed shortly after 7.30pm but was hit by a shake @-@ up - a sudden change in wind speed or direction over a short distance - and had to start through .
winds reached about 50 mph on the ground at Adelaide airport at that time .
the flight data showed the plane also had to go through a second landing flight and eventually set up at about 8.40 p.m.
the flight delay resulted in the delay of some other flights , including an Emirates flight from Dubai and a Quantas flight from Sydney .
for Adelaide , a maximum temperature of 16 ° C is predicted on Tuesday , with possible displays .
