his complaints , however , remained without diagnosis .
his health improved slowly and he returned to his workplace .
from time to time , however , symptoms returned , often after sporting activity and severe breathing .
in 2011 , a patient arrived with similar symptoms in his practice and was later diagnosed with mesothelioma .
but , even now , Abbott does not associate this with his own case .
after all , his patient was a few decades older and had worked directly with asbestos .
the connection in the case was clear .
in September 2011 , Abbott &apos;s condition deteriorated again and his family doctor brought his CT scans and X @-@ rays to an expert group .
in December 2011 , exactly two years after Abbott felt sick for the first time , a probe fitted with a camera was introduced into the cave between the rib and the chest .
I &apos;m an optimist .
I usually just continue , &quot; he says .
frankly , I hadn &apos;t worried so many at all .
