clever ways to save at university textbooks
since the cost of university textbooks is more than $ 1,000 a year for many students , the fast @-@ two @-@ year @-@ old student Matt Schroeder took over a clever savings idea .
he invented a surrogate system for books by students of higher semester and offered nominal compensation to delay the resale .
&quot; my math book usually costs $ 180 , but I got it for $ 10 for a semester and a Chick @-@ fil @-@ A @-@ Kek , &quot; said Schroeder , 19 , who attends Covenant College in Georgia .
the books needed for the last semester would have cost him $ 430 , he said .
he spent $ 120 .
the college newspaper announced that , on average , students spend more than $ 1,200 a year on textbooks and study material , but that there are different cost @-@ fighting options for students .
online stores and creative approaches like the Schroeders are increasingly the solution of choice for students .
hiring textbooks is becoming more popular , and students can use a book for a semester , often at a much cheaper price than when buying .
Neebo Inc , which operates more than 250 university bookstores , announced that rents of text books have doubled since 2011 .
surveys in the industry show that about a quarter of the books were rented in college bookstores last spring , Neebos Vice President Tevor Meyer said .
less than half of all textbooks are bought in campus bookstores , according to the Commerce Association of College Stores .
here &apos;s the one @-@ off for the best deals .
buy online
some new books cost online only one @-@ third of the price for which they are in campus bookstore .
the ninth edition of &quot; Calculus &quot; vno Ron Larwon , Bruce Edwards and Robert Hostetler costs nearly $ 290 , but can be obtained from the specialist textbook retailer Chegg.com for $ 239.99 .
buy needed
if one of the notes of other or normal utility tracks does not make up , used books are a good option .
&quot; calculus &quot; is needed on Chegg.com for $ 93.49 .
Matt Casaday , 25 , graduate student at Brigham Young University , says he has spent 42 cents on Amazon.com for a used edition of &quot; Strategic Media Decisions : understanding The Business End Of The Advertising Business . &quot;
the book was resold for $ 48 .
academics such as Ingrid Bracey , head of the University of Massachusetts at Amherst College Without Walls , advised students to ask at their professors whether previous expenses were permissible .
sometimes the updates for the seminar work are not relevant .
in such cases , older expenses can often be purchased for a fraction of the cost of the latest issue .
apart from Chegg and Amazon , Half.com of eBay Inc is also a popular alternative to used books .
rent
the rent of textbooks is worth a thought if you treat them reasonably well , remember to return them and you don &apos;t want to keep the books after completion of the course .
they can save more than 80 percent of the cost of a newly purchased book .
for example , a student could rent &quot; Calculus &quot; for about $ 20 for the duration of a semester .
find out about the terms of the business in which you rent , including the criminal charges that may apply to the writing of notes , undercuts or utility tracks .
tenants beware : if you don &apos;t return the book , the criminal charges may even exceed the price of a new book .
e @-@ Books
e @-@ books rather than traditional textbooks are also an option .
sometimes these books are de facto rented by providing an electronic license for a certain period of time from wholesalers such as Amazon.com , Chegg and Barnes &amp; Noble Inc .
at Chegg , you can rent &quot; Calculus &quot; for 6 months for about $ 61 .
Bracey says students in literary courses often find the best deals , since many classics can be downloaded for free nowadays , while scientific and engineering textbooks can be very expensive .
look around anyway .
Joe Gault , 29 , who will soon attend Pepperdine Law School , recommends the ISBN number for pricing on books , as you can be so sure to find the right textbook .
and before an online order , you should check , so Gault , if the book is actually preliminary .
he learned that lesson on the hard tour .
he bought a book that had four weeks delivery time and eventually paid the full price in the college bookshop .
