teenagers flown out of the Blue Mountains
two teenage bushmen were taken to safety with the rope winds after being caught the night over in the Blue Mountains in NSW .
the 16 @-@ year @-@ old girl and 19 @-@ year @-@ old man broke out on their tour shortly after Sunday afternoon in Gov. Leap in Blackheath .
worried relatives called police around 8pm when the two had not returned home .
a search of local police and emergency services broke down and the couple were found around 11pm near the Bridal Veil waterfalls .
the girl had been injured at the knee and the man was toppled and had his head beaten up .
rescuers stayed at the couple overnight and they were flown out on Monday morning .
they were delivered to Blue Mountains Hospital in stable condition with an ambulance .
