Renzi considers how the government @-@ run daily La Repubblica restates the appeal of his Mogherini , which is also a favorite in the government team , to strengthen the position of the Social Democrats and his own in the EU .
he also expects a boost to his &quot; reform package &quot; in Italy .
last but not least , Renzi hopes to calm down the left @-@ wing party base that he has repeatedly sought , because Mogherini is assigned - albeit more moderately - to this .
to the Conservative representatives with Commission President Jean @-@ Claude Juncker and Poland , nominated as President @-@ in @-@ Office of the Council , Donald Tusk , the dominant opinion in Rome , is to achieve political balance .
after all , the EU &apos;s chief diplomat will also become Deputy President Juncker .
the pending approval of the European Parliament is considered certain .
otherwise , President Giorgio Napolitano would have called the nomination of the 41year @-@ old politician of the ruling Democratic Party ( PD ) hardly an &quot; important recognition &quot; of Italy &apos;s role in the EU .
la Repubblica spreads optimism that the Mogherini , which has been proven for almost two decades in leading party offices and is known for its ambition , will rise to the &quot; enormous challenges . &quot;
the native Roman is married and has two daughters .
her party career began the doctorate in 1996 in the youth organisation of the then Democratici di Sinistra ( left @-@ wing democrat ) , which joined forces with the Catholic Centre party Margherita to present @-@ day social democratic PD in 2008 .
in 1999 , Mogherini became Vice @-@ President of the European Community Organisation of Socialist Youth ( European Young Socialists ) for three years .
with the 2001 election to the left @-@ wing Democratic Party , she rose to high party politics , working in the Foreign Policy Department , whose leader soon became her .
it has identified traditional priorities of Italian foreign policy , such as the Middle East , as well as studies of NATO deployment in Afghanistan involving Italy with a troop contingent , used contacts with social democrats in Europe and with US Democrats .
she has been a member of the Chamber of Deputies since 2008 , where she is an expert in defence and European and international affairs .
when Renzi became prime minister in February 2014 , he regretted Mogherini becoming his foreign minister .
once again , if the PD has a better relationship with the strong peace movement in the country , which contributed to the party &apos;s more than 40 per cent vote in the EU elections in May , Federica Mogherini will have a share of it .
the representations made in Brussels , the new EU external representatives have too little diplomatic experience , in other words lack substance , are countered in the PD .
in Brussels , particularly by Poland and the Baltic members , Mogherini &apos;s profoundly realistic accents of the crisis in Ukraine are being pursued and defamed as a &quot; country @-@ friendly course . &quot;
it supports the South Stream pipeline , which is operated by Russian firm Gazprom , through which Russian natural gas is to be transported directly to southern Europe , which also serves Italy &apos;s energy security .
after Renzi took office as EU chairman in July , Mogherini traveled to Moscow for her first state visit .
photos they showed with Putin at Shake hands were taken with indignation in Brussels , as well as that they invited the Kremlin leader to a Milan economic summit for October .
