Norwegian Cruise just ahead of a deal with Prestige Cruises of $ 3 billion
Norwegian Cruise Line Holdings Ltd NCHL.O , the world &apos;s third @-@ largest cruise operator , is conducting advanced negotiations to acquire rival Prestige Cruises International Inc for about $ 3 billion , according to industry experts .
a deal would give Norwegian Cruise , a company with a market value of $ 6.8 billion , access to Prestige Cruises &apos; luxury cruise ships as well as its wealthy clientele , while competing with larger rivals such as Royal Caribbean Cruises Ltd ( RCL.N ) and Carnival Corp ( CCL.N ) .
an agreement could be announced earlier this week , the sources said Sunday , and warned that the talks could also end without results .
the owner of Prestige Cruises , the private equity firm Apollo Global Management LLC ( APO.N ) also owns a 20 percent stake in Norwegian Cruise .
the sources asked to remain anonymous as negotiations were not public .
representatives of Norwegian Cruise and Prestige Cruises did not respond to requests for comment , while a spokesman for Apollo declined to comment .
Norwegian Cruise , a Miami @-@ based company , operates 13 cruise ships on routes between North America , the Mediterranean , the Baltic Sea , Central America and the Caribbean .
its revenue was $ 2.57 billion in 2013 , a 13 percent increase compared to 2012 .
Prestige Cruises , also based in Miami , operates under the brand names Oceania and Regent , which together operate eight cruise ships on routes to Scandinavia , Russia , the Mediterranean , North America , Asia , Africa and South America .
it reported revenue for 2013 of $ 1.2 billion , an increase of 6 percent compared with the previous year .
the cruise industry as a whole is about $ 29 billion and in the next few years it is expected to grow because of the strengthening of the middle class in emerging economies such as China and India .
the companies are trying to position themselves as the best choice among cruise operators for these new customers .
Prestige Cruises requested the IPO of US regulators in January 2014 .
Apollo has been the majority shareholder in the company for a $ 850 million deal in 2007 .
Norwegian Cruise was created in its current form in 2000 by a merger with a cruise carrier owned by Genting Bhd ( GENT.KL ) , a leisure and casino group under the control of Malaysian billionaire Lim Kok Thay .
Apollo invested $ 1 billion in Norwegian Cruise in 2008 .
Norwegian Cruise went to the stock market in January 2013 .
Genting held 28 percent of the stake in late June , according to approval ratings , Apollo 20 percent of the shares and the private equity firm TPG Capital LP held an 8 percent stake in the company .
Carnival , Royal Caribbean Cruises and Norwegian Cruise share more than 82 percent of passenger capacity on American cruise ships , according to the original order documents for Prestige Cruises .
pro @-@ Hong Kong activists condemn China the day after the election decision .
a pekingtreue group waved near the Chinese flag .
the permanent committee of the National People &apos;s Congress passed a framework law on Sunday allowing only two or three candidates for the leadership election in Hong Kong in 2017 .
all candidates must first obtain the majority support of a nominating committee , which is expected to be filled with peking members .
this decision makes it almost impossible for opposition Democrats to be allowed to vote , prompting pro @-@ democracy activists to make up their threat and paralyze Hong Kong &apos;s financial square with Occupy Central protests .
political reforms have long been a controversial issue in Hong Kong ; and China &apos;s party leadership fears that calls for democracy will spread to other cities .
after the publication of a Beijing White Paper outlining China &apos;s dominance of Hong Kong in June , democracy activists held an unofficial referendum on the electoral process in the Special Administrative Region , where hundreds of thousands marched in the city &apos;s business district and organized a sit @-@ in there .
Lis questioning is organised by the Hong Kong government and the Chinese liaison office in Hong Kong .
the Deputy Chairman of the Legal Affairs Commission of the Standing Committee , Zhang Rongshun , as well as the Deputy Director of the Office of Hong Kong and Macaus of the State Council , Feng Wei , should be consulted during the day .
student activists vowed to gather in front of the chief executive &apos;s office in Hong Kong in the afternoon .
Britain did not envisage any democratic elements until the end of the 150 @-@ year colonial government in Hong Kong .
Putin asks Kiev to begin &quot; statehood talks &quot; with eastern Ukraine
Russian President Vladimir Putin demanded Russian media reports on Sunday that the Ukrainian government suspend fighting against separatists in the east of the country and immediately begin negotiations on the &quot; statehood &quot; of the breakaway region .
his spokesman , Dimitri Peskov , later made it clear that Putin did not mean that the area of eastern Ukraine , under the control of the separatists , will become part of Russia , but that its status with Ukraine needs to be redefined in order to give the Russian @-@ speaking region the power to represent its rights and interests .
Putin &apos;s call to the Kiev government to negotiate on an equal footing with pro @-@ Russian insurgents , however , fits in with the strategy he appears to have pursued since the start of the riots five months ago : help the separatists to seize territory and pressure on the Ukrainian government to allow the newly proclaimed region of Novorossija de facto independence with Russia .
in an interview with state @-@ run television channel Eins , Putin condemned the Ukrainian military campaign to reclaim the territories held by separatists in the eastern regions of Donetsk and Luhansk , which were taken in March and April after Moscow annexed the Ukrainian peninsula of Crimea on March 18 .
the Kremlin and the separatists have recently called the captured area &quot; Novorossija &quot; or &quot; Neurussland , &quot; a term reminiscent of the pre @-@ revolutionary glamour of the Russian empire .
Putin pointed out that all those who , in the course of the campaigns of Ukrainian politicians for the elections on 26 Oct. and while government groups are attacking civilian communities in the areas held by separatists , are hoping for early peace talks &quot; caught in their illusions , &quot; Itar @-@ Tass reported .
&quot; we need to start detailed talks immediately , not only on technical issues , but also on the political organization of society and the state status of South @-@ Eastern Ukraine , to preserve the interests of the people living there , &quot; he said .
Peskov said Putin &apos;s reference to statehood in the context of greater autonomy , which has been discussed for months by the Kiev leadership to allay fears in Russian @-@ speaking areas that their cultural and linguistic rights are at risk .
only the Ukrainian government can provide the necessary autonomy to the eastern areas , Peskov said .
this is not about negotiations between Ukraine and Russia , Peskov said , &quot; because it is not about a conflict between Russia and Ukraine , but about an internal conflict in Ukraine . &quot;
the Kremlin &apos;s clarification on the correction of Putin &apos;s remarks &quot; misinterpretation &quot; underlined Russia &apos;s leadership in dealing with the separatist rebellion in the east , unlike the direct annexation of Crimea , on which the majority of the 2 million inhabitants are ethnic Russians .
Moscow would have far greater difficulty in annexing the regions of Donetsk and Luhansk in eastern Ukraine , as most of the 6.5 million inhabitants are not Russians and polls from the period before the conflict gave a broad majority to stay in Ukraine .
the autonomy raised by Russian diplomats at international forums would give regional governments in Ukraine authority to negotiate their own trade agreements and external relations , and thus give the Kremlin de facto control over an area linking the Russian territory with Crimea .
the peninsula annexed to the Black Sea five months ago is the home port for most of the Russian navy , as well as a major commercial and historical coastal region .
the regions between the Rostowland region in Russia and Crimea are also rich in mines , factories and foundries that produce important components for the Russian military .
Ukrainian President Petro Poroshenko , in his speech on inauguration on 7 June , suggested that Ukrainian legislation , after new elections , should consider additions to the constitution giving greater control to the respective territories over their finances and the status of languages .
but his idea of autonomy seems to be in sharp contrast to those of the Kremlin and separatist rebels whose arming and incitement Moscow is accused of .
Putin &apos;s latest call for Kiev to negotiate with separatist leaders on an equal footing followed a further push by the rebels last week after Russian troops and tanks invaded eastern Ukraine over the previously peaceful region along the Asov Sea .
Russia @-@ backed separatists took control of Nowoasowsk , according to fears Ukrainian security officials are the first step in a campaign to take over the strategic coastal region to Crimea .
for this reason , massive civilian and military preparations have been under way to consolidate Mariupol , a steel industry with 500,000 inhabitants , located between Nowoasowsk and narrow access to Crimea Peninsula .
Poroshenko spoke at a meeting of EU leaders in Brussels on Saturday and urged action to prevent further Russian aggression against Ukraine , a former Soviet republic who has been independent for 23 years .
&quot; we are on the verge of a point where there is no going back , &quot; Poroshenko warned .
thousands of foreign troops and hundreds of foreign tanks are now on Ukraine &apos;s territory .
the EU summit decided not to take concrete action , and the leadership called for further sanctions against Russia to enter into force in an unspecified escalation of the Ukrainian crisis .
Ukrainian soldiers had to withdraw from their positions in Ilowajsk after two Russian tank fighters and 1,000 soldiers entered the Donetsk region last week to support the besieged separatists , Colonel Andrij Lysenko , spokesman for Ukraine &apos;s National Security and Defence Council , said Saturday in Kiev .
the first likely 63 Ukrainian soldiers included by the Russian incursion into Ilowajsk were replaced on Sunday against 10 Russian parachute hunters who had been captured on Ukrainian territory a week ago , Lysenko said Sunday .
